.TH bcopy 3 (date) "Linux man-pages (unreleased)"
.SH NAME
bcopy \- copy byte sequence
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C library
.RI ( libc ,\~ \-lc )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <strings.h>
.P
.BI "[[deprecated]] void bcopy(size_t " n ;
.BI "                          const void " src [ n "], void " dest [ n "], \
size_t " n );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR bcopy ()
function copies
.I n
bytes from
.I src
to
.IR dest .
The result is correct, even when both areas overlap.
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
